<p class="no-box"><b>This will be updated frequently.</b><br>


<h3>Week One</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
<li><b>Class 1</b> (Monday, March 28):  Introduction to the course.
  Introductory discussion of 
  energy, conservation of energy, and power. 
<!--<li><b>Lab 1</b>:  Measurement and watt meters.  -->
<li><b>Class 2</b> (Thursday, March 31): Read Chapter 1
  of <a href="http://withouthotair.com/">SEWTHA</a> (MacKay) and the
  Preface of <a href="./Textbook/energybook.pdf">SEFAS</a> (Feldman
  and Demeo). Bring questions and comments on the MacKay reading.
  In class we will discuss the reading and go further into energy and
  power.    
<li><b><a href="./Homework/homework.1.pdf">Homework One</a></b> due on
  Friday, April 1. 
</ul>
<br>

<h3>Week Two</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
<li><b>Class 3</b> (Monday, April 4):  Initial discussion of windpower
  and areas. 
<li><b>Class 4</b> (Thursday, April 7): Anna's presentation on wind
  and the grid.
</ul>
<br>

<h3>Week Three</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
<li><b>Class 5</b> (Monday, April 11):  Windpower conclusion.  Basics
  of electricity generation.
<li><b><a href="./Homework/homework.2.pdf">Homework Two</a></b> due on
  Tuesday, April 12.  
<li><b>Class 6</b> (Thursday, April 14): Solar photovoltaics.
<li><b><a href="./Homework/homework.3.pdf">Homework Three</a></b> due
  on Friday, April 15.
</ul>
<br>

<h3>Week Four</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
<li><b>Class 7</b> (Monday, April 18): Finish solar.  Start cars and
  planes.  <a href="http://www.inference.eng.cam.ac.uk/sustainable/book/tex/RSsolar.pdf">Link</a>
  to the solar paper we discussed in class.
<li><b>Class 8</b> (Thursday, April 21): More cars and other
  transport.  Start time value of money?
<li><b><a href="./Homework/homework.4.pdf">Homework Four</a></b> due
  on Friday, April 22. 
</ul><br>

<h3>Week Five</h3><p class ="no-box">
<ul>
<li><b>Class 9</b> (Monday, April 25): Time Value of Monday.
<li><b>Class 10</b> (Thursday, April 28): Valuing Investments (payback
  time, ROI, IRR)
<li><b><a href="./Homework/homework.5.pdf">Homework
    Five</a></b> due on Friday, April 29.  
</ul><br>


<h3>Week Six</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
  <li><b>Class 11</b> (Monday, May 2) Finish investment valuation.
  Start thermal energy. 
  <li><b>Class 12</b> (Thursday, May 5)   Solar Thermal.  Nuclear basics
  <li><b><a hfre="./Homework/homework.6.pdf">Homework Six</a></b> due on Friday, May 6.
</ul>
</p>

<h3>Week Seven</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
  <li><b>Class 13</b> (Monday, May 9)  Nuclear power guest lecture.
  <li><b><a href="Homework/finance_exercise.pdf">Finance
  Exercise</a></b> due on Tuesday, May 10.
  <li><b>Class 14</b> (Thursday, May 12) Home heating: Dealing with Leakiness. 
  <li><b><a href="Homework/homework.7.pdf">Homework 7</a></b> due on
  Friday, May 13.
</ul>
</p>

<h3>Week Eight</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
  <li><b>Class 15</b> (Monday, May 16) Home heating: Generating Heat.
  Combined heat and Power.  Heat Pumps. 
  <li><b>Class 16</b> (Friday, May 19) Agriculture
  <li><b><a href="Homework/homework.8.pdf">Homework 8</a></b> due on
  Friday, May 20.
</ul>
</p>

<h3>Week Nine</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
  <li><b>Class 17</b> (Monday, May 23) Making stuff.
  <li><b>Class 18</b> (Friday, May 26) Negative carbon emissions
  <li><b><a href="Homework/homework.9.pdf">Homework 9</a></b> due on
  Friday, May 27.
</ul>
</p>

<h3>Week Ten</h3><p class="no-box">
<ul>
  <li><b>Class 19</b> (Monday, May 30) Carbon capture and storage
     and negative carbon emissions.
  <li><b>Class 20</b> (Friday, June 2) Big picture/summary/conclusions
  <li><b><a>Homework 10</a></b> due on Friday, June 3.
